ger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever goes to the gates of the ruler will be put to trial. A servant does not move closer to the ruler but that he moves further away from Allah.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 8836 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32741,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/11\/beware-gates-sultan\/","url_meta":{"origin":27463,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Rulers: Beware associating with tyrannical, unjust rulers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu al-\u2018Awar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBeware of approaching the gates of the ruler, for they will become tyrants.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n lil-Bayhaqi\u0304 8786 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0651\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0645\u0650\u064a\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":18429,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/06\/nasihah-imams-private\/","url_meta":{"origin":27463,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Rulers: Advise misguided leaders in private if possible","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 6, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Iyad ibn Ghanam reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever has advice for the ruler, let him take his hand and give it privately. If he accepts it, then he accepts it. If he rejects it, the duty upon him has been fulfilled.\" Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17907,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/27\/sabr-with-sultan\/","url_meta":{"origin":27463,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Sultan: Be patient with tyranny from your rulers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 27, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever sees something from his ruler that he hates, let him be patient. Whoever secedes from the community by as much as a handspan and dies will have died a death of ignorance.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":38857,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/02\/21\/dua-oppressive-ruler\/","url_meta":{"origin":27463,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Sultan: Supplication when fearing an oppressive ruler","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 21, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Harith ibn Suwayd reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIf a leader is appointed over you from whom you fear arrogance or injustice, let him say: O Allah, Lord of the seven heavens, Lord of the Mighty Throne, be my protector against this man, the\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19388,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/06\/21\/pardon-hudud-if-possible\/","url_meta":{"origin":27463,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Hudud: Pardon criminal before notifying ruler, if possible","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 21, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPardon the legal punishments between yourselves, for whatever offense reaches me must be punished.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4376 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u0650\u0648 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0635\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuami